{
  "texts": [
    "Unlike True/False and MCQ formats, one-word questions offer a more robust means of assessment because they minimize the possibility of random guessing.",
    "Evaluation MethodologyWe evaluated all 6 models on TALES-QA to assess their cultural knowledge.",
    "To prevent models from producing long-form responses, we provided instructions tailored to each question type.",
    "To mitigate potential false negatives arising from Unicode or script matching issues in Indic languages, and following the recent success of auto raters for answer matching [18], we used GPT 4o as a judge to compare each model's responses against the correct answers (prompt provided in Appendix H).",
    "Additionally, to capture variability and uncertainty in model outputs, we sampled five responses from the model being tested and computed average across all of them."
  ]
}